{
  "texts": [
    "In this example, we consider the following one-dimensional SDE:(4.2) dXt = κ(η -Xt-) dt + σ dBt + dL α t,which has been widely used to capture dynamics with both continuous fluctuations and heavy-tailed, discontinuous shocks, making them relevant in fields such as finance, physics [2], and generative modeling [42].",
    "This system captures mean reversion, diffusion, and an α-stable Lévy motion L α t with Lévy measure:ν(r) = cα 1 |r| α+1, cα = α 2 1-α √ π Γ( 1+α 2) Γ(1 -α 2), Γ(z):= ∞ 0 t z-1 e -t dt.",
    "We set α = 1.5 while keeping all other hyperparameters the same as in Example 1.",
    "To avoid the singularity of the intensity measure ν at 0, the numerical integration with respect to ν(r) is restricted to the interval [-5, -0.01] ∪ [0.01, 5].",
    "In this example, the Monte Carlo simulation is based on the following Euler-Maruyama scheme:X (i) t+∆t = X (i) t + κ(η -X (i) t)∆t + σξ t + ∆L α t, i = 1, • • •, N, where the jump increments ∆L α t = L α t+∆t -L α t follow a stable distribution S α (∆t 1 α, 0, 0)."
  ]
}